A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Sheriff's Klean Initiative Program (S.K.I.P.) Unit; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Sheriff's Klean Initiative Program (S.K.I.P.) Unit is a specialized division
4 within the Clayton County Sheriff's Office responsible for managing inmate work details that
5 focus on community beautification and maintenance projects; and
6 WHEREAS, the S.K.I.P. Unit provides non-violent offenders with opportunities for
7 rehabilitation and skill-building by engaging them in tasks such as trash collection,
8 landscaping, minor repairs, and facility upkeep throughout Clayton County; and
9 WHEREAS, the program enhances public spaces and fosters a sense of responsibility among
10 participants while contributing to the overall cleanliness and maintenance of the county; and
11 WHEREAS, the commitment of the S.K.I.P. Unit to both community improvement and
12 offender rehabilitation exemplifies the positive impact of structured reintegration programs
13 within the criminal justice system; and
